---
import Layout from '../layouts/layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Cookie Policy"
  htmlClassName="no-js"
  description="Hindalco cookie policy."
>
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-10 md:py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-semibold text-secondary leading-tight mb-8">
      Cookie Policy
    </h1>
    <div class="space-y-4 text-neutral-800 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Hindalco Industries Limited (hereinafter referred to as “Hindalco”,
        “we”, “us”, “our”) uses cookies across its websites to improve
        performance and enhance the experience. This policy explains how we do
        that.
      </p>
      <p>
        Cookies are small text files which are placed on your electronic devices
        by a web server/ website. The cookie will help the website recognise
        you, from amongst other users. We may place cookies on the users’
        electronic devices, when they interact with us. We cannot use them to
        deliver viruses on to users’ devices or use it for the purposes of
        accessing their hard drive.
      </p>
      <p>&nbsp;The data generated from the cookies will be used for the following purposes, by us:</p>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-3">
        <li>
          Strictly necessary – these cookies are essential, and they facilitate
          your movement on the website, access the content, and use its
          features, such as accessing secure areas of the website. Without these
          cookies, we will not be able to provide the user the services they
          seek.
        </li>
        <li>
          Analytics cookies – these cookies enable us to measure and improve the
          performance of our website and provide more relevant content to the
          user. These cookies do not pass on personally identifiable
          information, and do not identify you to an individual level.
        </li>
        <li>
          Performance cookies – these are generally third-party cookies from
          third party service providers we work with, or who on our behalf
          collect information about your interaction/ visits on our website and
          help with identifying if you receive error messages from any website,
          or which pages you visit more often. Third party vendors may have
          access to this data and may use it to improve their overall services
          and offerings. These cookies do not collect information to identify
          you.
        </li>
        <li>
          Functionality cookies – these cookies help our website to remember
          choices like the preferred language, region you are in, and provide
          you with enhanced features. These cannot track user’s activity on
          other websites, and they do not gather information about the user,
          which can be used for advertising or noting what the user may have
          accessed over the internet outside of our website.
        </li>
        <li>
          Advertising and social media cookies – these cookies are used to
          deliver (i) targeted advertisements; (ii) control the times you watch
          an advertisement; (iii) measure the effectiveness of our advertising
          campaigns; (iv) understand user’s behaviour after their viewing of
          the advertisement.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-secondary pt-2">
        How can you block cookies?
      </h2>
      <p>
        Hindalco is required by the applicable laws to seek your consent to be
        able to place any other than those which are strictly necessary. You can
        control whether to accept cookies or not and adjust your preferences
        through our cookie consent manager. If you decide to not accept cookies,
        some features and services on our websites will not function properly.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you would prefer not to accept cookies you can either change your
        browser settings to notify you when you receive a cookie, which lets you
        choose whether or not to accept it; or, set your browser to
        automatically not accept any cookies. You can manage cookies in the
        privacy settings of the web browser you are using. You can refer to this
        for more information: http://www.aboutcookies.org/.
      </p>
      <p>
        To modify your cookie preference click on
        <a
          href="https://consent.trustarc.com/v2/notice/po5ejq"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-primary hover:underline"
        >
          Cookie Preference
        </a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        For more information on how we handle personal information please refer
        to our <a href="https://www.hindalco.com/data-privacy-policy" class="text-primary hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>